commit.message:
Fix loading edge case STMs with an EOF byte of 2. (#701)

All STMs should have 0x1a as their EOF byte, but two broken STM
modules "putup10.stm" and "putup11.stm" have a value of 2 here
instead. This patch allows those modules to load.

commit.message:
Bug fixes to DSMI loader (#690)

Bug fixes to DSMI loader, which fixes these bugs:

- Did always set the calculated panning on the first channel, so it will contain the last calculated value while the rest will have default values.
- For version 11 modules, the loader skip the panning values as it think it's channel remappings. Version 11 also only have 16 panning values while version 12 and higher have 32.
- Could not load version 12 modules, since it did not load the panning values (not tested, since I do not have any modules in this version, but according to Ottos code, version 12 should have 32 bytes of panning values, but libxmp only loaded 16 bytes as channel remaps).
- Added extra unit test for version 13.

commit.message:
Faster IT loading by buffering pattern, sample, and comment reads. (#694)

The IT format stores 16-bit lengths for patterns and compressed sample
blocks, which allows both to be loaded into a buffer to be read from
memory. This patch adds a 64k temporary buffer to the IT loader to
reduce load times for this format.

The average improvement in my loose measurements is about 45.5%
(measured by loading every file in the Modland IT directory once with
xmpchk: Windows 10 x86_64, all files buffered by the kernel, all files
read into memory and loaded with `xmp_load_module_from_memory`).
This is going to vary based on the structure of any given file.

|       | master (16fc5c89) | Patch      |
|-------|-------------------|------------|
| Run 1 | 3m34.269s         | 1m56.595s  |
| Run 2 | 3m34.537s         | 1m56.572s  |
| Run 3 | 3m34.021s         | 1m57.067s  |
| Avg.  | 3m34.276s         | 1m56.745s  |

Further testing in Fedora and some additional testing by ds-sloth on
the 3DS verifies these performance improvements.

commit.message:
Fix an extra scan edge case related to scan edge case fix #688. (#692)

If two sequences jump to the same invalid/skip pattern immediately
prior to the end of the module, the previous scan fix patch would
attempt to read the order list out-of-bounds. I've fixed this by
just making the invalid/skip pattern handling part of the same
branch as the S3M_END handling in the fix, which I should have done
anyway.

commit.message:
Fix loop detection edge cases broken by S3M/IT marker scan bugs. (#688)

* "alien incident - leohou2.s3m" by Purple Motion had broken loop
  detection in sequence 8 due to it using a pattern jump to an end
  marker associated with sequence 7. Fixed by handling end markers
  in the scan regardless of which sequence they are attached to.
* "amazonas-dynomite mix.it" by Skaven had broken loop detection in
  sequence 9 caused by the scan placing its loop point inside of a
  nonexistent marker "pattern". Fixed by placing the loop point at
  the start of the first real pattern in a sequence.
